{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":0,"text":"There's a great big elephant in the room called the economy."},{"time":4000,"text":"So let's start talking about that."},{"time":6000,"text":"I wanted to give you a current picture of the economy."},{"time":9000,"text":"That's what I have behind myself."}]},{"cues":[{"time":12000,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":15000,"text":"But of course what we have to remember is this."},{"time":18000,"text":"And what you have to think about is,"},{"time":21000,"text":"when you're dancing in the flames, what's next?"},{"time":24000,"text":"So what I'm going to try to do in the next 17 and a half minutes"},{"time":27000,"text":"is I'm going to talk first about the flames --"},{"time":29000,"text":"where we are in the economy --"},{"time":31000,"text":"and then I'm going to take three trends"},{"time":33000,"text":"that have taken place at TED over the last 25 years"},{"time":36000,"text":"and that will take place in this conference"},{"time":38000,"text":"and I will try and bring them together."},{"time":41000,"text":"And I will try and give you a sense of what the ultimate reboot looks like."},{"time":45000,"text":"Those three trends are"},{"time":47000,"text":"the ability to engineer cells,"},{"time":49000,"text":"the ability to engineer tissues,"},{"time":51000,"text":"and robots."},{"time":53000,"text":"And somehow it will all make sense."}]},{"cues":[{"time":55000,"text":"But anyway, let's start with the economy."},{"time":58000,"text":"There's a couple of really big problems that are still sitting there."},{"time":61000,"text":"One is leverage."},{"time":63000,"text":"And the problem with leverage is"},{"time":65000,"text":"it makes the U.S. financial system look like this."}]},{"cues":[{"time":68000,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":75000,"text":"So, a normal commercial bank has nine to 10 times leverage."},{"time":78000,"text":"That means for every dollar you deposit, it loans out about nine or 10."},{"time":81000,"text":"A normal investment bank is not a deposit bank,"},{"time":84000,"text":"it's an investment bank;"},{"time":86000,"text":"it has 15 to 20 times."},{"time":88000,"text":"It turns out that B of A in September had 32 times."},{"time":91000,"text":"And your friendly Citibank had 47 times."},{"time":94000,"text":"Oops."},{"time":96000,"text":"That means every bad loan goes bad 47 times over."},{"time":100000,"text":"And that, of course, is the reason why all of you"},{"time":103000,"text":"are making such generous and wonderful donations"},{"time":106000,"text":"to these nice folks."},{"time":111000,"text":"And as you think about that,"},{"time":113000,"text":"you've got to wonder: so what do banks have in store for you now?"},{"time":119000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":128000,"text":"It ain't pretty."}]},{"cues":[{"time":131000,"text":"The government, meanwhile, has been acting like Santa Claus."},{"time":135000,"text":"We all love Santa Claus, right?"},{"time":138000,"text":"But the problem with Santa Clause is,"},{"time":141000,"text":"if you look at the mandatory spending of what these folks have been doing"},{"time":144000,"text":"and promising folks,"},{"time":146000,"text":"it turned out that in 1967, 38 percent was mandatory spending"},{"time":151000,"text":"on what we call \"entitlements.\""},{"time":154000,"text":"And then by 2007 it was 68 percent."},{"time":157000,"text":"And we weren't supposed to run into 100 percent until about 2030."},{"time":162000,"text":"Except we've been so busy giving away a trillion here, a trillion there,"},{"time":165000,"text":"that we've brought that date of reckoning forward\n"},{"time":168000,"text":"to about 2017."},{"time":171000,"text":"And we thought we were going to be able to lay these debts off on our kids,"},{"time":174000,"text":"but, guess what?"},{"time":176000,"text":"We're going to start to pay them."},{"time":178000,"text":"And the problem with this stuff is, now that the bill's come due,"},{"time":180000,"text":"it turns out Santa isn't quite as cute when it's summertime."},{"time":184000,"text":"Right?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":186000,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":198000,"text":"Here's some advice from one of the largest investors in the United States."},{"time":202000,"text":"This guy runs the China Investment Corporation."},{"time":205000,"text":"He is the main buyer of U.S. Treasury bonds."},{"time":208000,"text":"And he gave an interview in December."},{"time":211000,"text":"Here's his first bit of advice."},{"time":213000,"text":"And here's his second bit of advice."},{"time":218000,"text":"And, by the way,"},{"time":220000,"text":"the Chinese Prime Minister reiterated this at Davos last Sunday."},{"time":223000,"text":"This stuff is getting serious enough"},{"time":225000,"text":"that if we don't start paying attention to the deficit,"},{"time":227000,"text":"we're going to end up losing the dollar."},{"time":230000,"text":"And then all bets are off."}]},{"cues":[{"time":233000,"text":"Let me show you what it looks like."},{"time":236000,"text":"I think I can safely say"},{"time":238000,"text":"that I'm the only trillionaire in this room."},{"time":242000,"text":"This is an actual bill."},{"time":244000,"text":"And it's 10 triliion dollars."},{"time":247000,"text":"The only problem with this bill is it's not really worth very much."},{"time":250000,"text":"That was eight bucks last week, four bucks this week,"},{"time":253000,"text":"a buck next week."},{"time":255000,"text":"And that's what happens to currencies when you don't stand behind them."},{"time":260000,"text":"So the next time somebody as cute as this shows up on your doorstep,"},{"time":265000,"text":"and sometimes this creature's called Chrysler and sometimes Ford and sometimes ... whatever you want --"},{"time":272000,"text":"you've just got to say no."},{"time":274000,"text":"And you've got to start banishing a word that's called \"entitlement.\""},{"time":278000,"text":"And the reason we have to do that in the short term"},{"time":281000,"text":"is because we have just run out of cash."}]},{"cues":[{"time":284000,"text":"If you look at the federal budget, this is what it looks like."},{"time":287000,"text":"The orange slice is what's discretionary."},{"time":290000,"text":"Everything else is mandated."},{"time":293000,"text":"It makes no difference if we cut out the bridges to Alaska in the overall scheme of things."},{"time":296000,"text":"So what we have to start thinking about doing"},{"time":299000,"text":"is capping our medical spending"},{"time":301000,"text":"because that's a monster that's simply going to eat the entire budget."},{"time":304000,"text":"We've got to start thinking about asking people"},{"time":307000,"text":"to retire a little bit later."},{"time":310000,"text":"If you're 60 to 65 you retire on time."},{"time":313000,"text":"Your 401(k) just got nailed."},{"time":315000,"text":"If you're 50 to 60 we want you to work two years more."},{"time":318000,"text":"If you're under 50 we want you to work four more years."},{"time":321000,"text":"The reason why that's reasonable is,"},{"time":324000,"text":"when your grandparents were given Social Security,"},{"time":326000,"text":"they got it at 65 and were expected to check out at 68."},{"time":329000,"text":"Sixty-eight is young today."},{"time":332000,"text":"We've also got to cut the military about three percent a year."}]},{"cues":[{"time":336000,"text":"We've got to limit other mandatory spending."},{"time":338000,"text":"We've got to quit borrowing as much,"},{"time":341000,"text":"because otherwise the interest is going to eat that whole pie."},{"time":344000,"text":"And we've got to end up with a smaller government."},{"time":346000,"text":"And if we don't start changing this trend line,"},{"time":349000,"text":"we are going to lose the dollar"},{"time":351000,"text":"and start to look like Iceland."},{"time":353000,"text":"I got what you're thinking."},{"time":356000,"text":"This is going to happen when hell freezes over."},{"time":361000,"text":"But let me remind you this December it did snow in Vegas."}]},{"cues":[{"time":366000,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":371000,"text":"Here's what happens if you don't address this stuff."},{"time":374000,"text":"So, Japan had a fiscal real estate crisis"},{"time":377000,"text":"back in the late '80s."},{"time":379000,"text":"And its 225 largest companies today"},{"time":382000,"text":"are worth one quarter of what they were 18 years ago."},{"time":385000,"text":"We don't fix this now,"},{"time":387000,"text":"how would you like to see a Dow 3,500 in 2026?"},{"time":390000,"text":"Because that's the consequence of not dealing with this stuff."},{"time":393000,"text":"And unless you want this person"},{"time":396000,"text":"to not just become the CFO of Florida, but the United States,"},{"time":399000,"text":"we'd better deal with this stuff."},{"time":402000,"text":"That's the short term. That's the flame part."},{"time":405000,"text":"That's the financial crisis."}]},{"cues":[{"time":407000,"text":"Now, right behind the financial crisis there's a second and bigger wave"},{"time":411000,"text":"that we need to talk about."},{"time":412000,"text":"That wave is much larger, much more powerful,"},{"time":414000,"text":"and that's of course the wave of technology."},{"time":417000,"text":"And what's really important in this stuff is,"},{"time":419000,"text":"as we cut, we also have to grow."},{"time":421000,"text":"Among other things, because startup companies"},{"time":424000,"text":"are .02 percent of U.S. GDP investmentm"},{"time":426000,"text":"and they're about 17.8 percent of output."},{"time":431000,"text":"It's groups like that in this room that generate the future of the U.S. economy."},{"time":434000,"text":"And that's what we've got to keep growing."},{"time":436000,"text":"We don't have to keep growing these bridges to nowhere."},{"time":440000,"text":"So let's bring a romance novelist into this conversation."},{"time":446000,"text":"And that's where these three trends come together."},{"time":451000,"text":"That's where the ability to engineer microbes,"},{"time":454000,"text":"the ability to engineer tissues,"},{"time":456000,"text":"and the ability to engineer robots"},{"time":458000,"text":"begin to lead to a reboot."},{"time":460000,"text":"And let me recap some of the stuff you've seen."}]},{"cues":[{"time":462000,"text":"Craig Venter showed up last year"},{"time":464000,"text":"and showed you the first fully programmable cell that acts like hardware"},{"time":466000,"text":"where you can insert DNA and have it boot up as a different species."},{"time":469000,"text":"In parallel, the folks at MIT"},{"time":472000,"text":"have been building a standard registry of biological parts."},{"time":475000,"text":"So think of it as a Radio Shack for biology."},{"time":478000,"text":"You can go out and get your proteins, your RNA, your DNA, whatever."},{"time":481000,"text":"And start building stuff."},{"time":484000,"text":"In 2006 they brought together high school students and college students"},{"time":487000,"text":"and started to build these little odd creatures."},{"time":489000,"text":"They just happened to be alive instead of circuit boards."}]},{"cues":[{"time":492000,"text":"Here was one of the first things they built."},{"time":495000,"text":"So, cells have this cycle."},{"time":497000,"text":"First they don't grow."},{"time":499000,"text":"Then they grow exponentially."},{"time":501000,"text":"Then they stop growing."},{"time":503000,"text":"Graduate students wanted a way of telling which stage they were in."},{"time":506000,"text":"So they engineered these cells"},{"time":508000,"text":"so that when they're growing in the exponential phase,"},{"time":510000,"text":"they would smell like wintergreen."},{"time":512000,"text":"And when they stopped growing they would smell like bananas."},{"time":515000,"text":"And you could tell very easily when your experiment was working"},{"time":518000,"text":"and wasn't, and where it was in the phase."}]},{"cues":[{"time":521000,"text":"This got a bit more complicated two years later."},{"time":524000,"text":"Twenty-one countries came together. Dozens of teams."},{"time":526000,"text":"They started competing."},{"time":528000,"text":"The team from Rice University started to engineer the substance in red wine"},{"time":533000,"text":"that makes red wine good for you"},{"time":535000,"text":"into beer."},{"time":538000,"text":"So you take resveratrol and you put it into beer."},{"time":542000,"text":"Of course, one of the judges is wandering by, and he goes,"},{"time":545000,"text":"\"Wow! Cancer-fighting beer! There is a God.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":549000,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":552000,"text":"The team from Taiwan was a little bit more ambitious."},{"time":555000,"text":"They tried to engineer bacterias in such a way"},{"time":558000,"text":"that they would act as your kidneys."},{"time":561000,"text":"Four years ago, I showed you this picture."},{"time":564000,"text":"And people oohed and ahhed,"},{"time":566000,"text":"because Cliff Tabin had been able to grow an extra wing on a chicken."},{"time":569000,"text":"And that was very cool stuff back then."},{"time":572000,"text":"But now moving from bacterial engineering to tissue engineering,"},{"time":575000,"text":"let me show you what's happened in that period of time."}]},{"cues":[{"time":578000,"text":"Two years ago, you saw this creature."},{"time":581000,"text":"An almost-extinct animal from Xochimilco, Mexico"},{"time":584000,"text":"called an axolotl"},{"time":586000,"text":"that can re-generate its limbs."},{"time":588000,"text":"You can freeze half its heart. It regrows."},{"time":590000,"text":"You can freeze half the brain. It regrows."},{"time":592000,"text":"It's almost like leaving Congress."},{"time":594000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":600000,"text":"But now, you don't have to have the animal itself to regenerate,"},{"time":603000,"text":"because you can build cloned mice molars in Petri dishes."},{"time":609000,"text":"And, of course if you can build mice molars in Petri dishes,"},{"time":613000,"text":"you can grow human molars in Petri dishes."},{"time":616000,"text":"This should not surprise you, right?"},{"time":618000,"text":"I mean, you're born with no teeth."},{"time":620000,"text":"You give away all your teeth to the tooth fairy."},{"time":623000,"text":"You re-grow a set of teeth."},{"time":625000,"text":"But then if you lose one of those second set of teeth, they don't regrow,"},{"time":628000,"text":"unless, if you're a lawyer."}]},{"cues":[{"time":630000,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":634000,"text":"But, of course, for most of us,"},{"time":637000,"text":"we know how to grow teeth, and therefore we can take adult stem teeth,"},{"time":640000,"text":"put them on a biodegradable mold, re-grow a tooth,"},{"time":643000,"text":"and simply implant it."},{"time":644000,"text":"And we can do it with other things."},{"time":647000,"text":"So, a Spanish woman who was dying of T.B. had a donor trachea,"},{"time":652000,"text":"they took all the cells off the trachea,"},{"time":654000,"text":"they spraypainted her stem cells onto that cartilage."},{"time":657000,"text":"She regrew her own trachea,"},{"time":659000,"text":"and 72 hours later it was implanted."},{"time":662000,"text":"She's now running around with her kids."},{"time":664000,"text":"This is going on in Tony Atala's lab in Wake Forest"},{"time":667000,"text":"where he is re-growing ears for injured soldiers,"},{"time":670000,"text":"and he's also re-growing bladders."},{"time":674000,"text":"So there are now nine women walking around Boston"},{"time":677000,"text":"with re-grown bladders,"},{"time":679000,"text":"which is much more pleasant than walking around with a whole bunch of plastic bags"},{"time":681000,"text":"for the rest of your life."}]},{"cues":[{"time":683000,"text":"This is kind of getting boring, right?"},{"time":686000,"text":"I mean, you understand where this story's going."},{"time":688000,"text":"But, I mean it gets more interesting."},{"time":690000,"text":"Last year, this group was able to take all the cells off a heart,"},{"time":694000,"text":"leaving just the cartilage."},{"time":697000,"text":"Then, they sprayed stem cells onto that heart, from a mouse."},{"time":699000,"text":"Those stem cells self-organized, and that heart started to beat."},{"time":703000,"text":"Life happens."}]},{"cues":[{"time":707000,"text":"This may be one of the ultimate papers."},{"time":710000,"text":"This was done in Japan and in the U.S., published at the same time,"},{"time":713000,"text":"and it rebooted skin cells into stem cells, last year."},{"time":718000,"text":"That meant that you can take the stuff right here,"},{"time":721000,"text":"and turn it into almost anything in your body."},{"time":723000,"text":"And this is becoming common, it's moving very quickly,"},{"time":726000,"text":"it's moving in a whole series of places."}]},{"cues":[{"time":730000,"text":"Third trend: robots."},{"time":733000,"text":"Those of us of a certain age grew up expecting that by now"},{"time":736000,"text":"we would have Rosie the Robot from \"The Jetsons\" in our house."},{"time":740000,"text":"And all we've got is a Roomba."},{"time":743000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":746000,"text":"We also thought we'd have this robot to warn us of danger."},{"time":750000,"text":"Didn't happen."},{"time":752000,"text":"And these were robots engineered for a flat world, right?"},{"time":755000,"text":"So, Rosie runs around on skates"},{"time":757000,"text":"and the other one ran on flat threads."},{"time":760000,"text":"If you don't have a flat world, that's not good,"},{"time":762000,"text":"which is why the robot's we're designing today are a little different."}]},{"cues":[{"time":768000,"text":"This is Boston Dynamics' \"BigDog.\""},{"time":773000,"text":"And this is about as close as you can get to a physical Turing test."},{"time":776000,"text":"O.K., so let me remind you, a Turing test is where you've got a wall,"},{"time":780000,"text":"you're talking to somebody on the other side of the wall,"},{"time":782000,"text":"and when you don't know if that thing is human or animal --"},{"time":785000,"text":"that's when computers have reached human intelligence."},{"time":789000,"text":"This is not an intelligence Turing rest,"},{"time":792000,"text":"but this is as close as you can get to a physical Turing test."},{"time":795000,"text":"And this stuff is moving very quickly,"},{"time":797000,"text":"and by the way, that thing can carry about 350 pounds of weight."},{"time":802000,"text":"These are not the only interesting robots."},{"time":805000,"text":"You've also got flies, the size of flies,"},{"time":807000,"text":"that are being made by Robert Wood at Harvard."},{"time":810000,"text":"You've got Stickybots that are being made at Stanford."},{"time":813000,"text":"And as you bring these things together,"},{"time":816000,"text":"as you bring cells, biological tissue engineering and mechanics together,"},{"time":822000,"text":"you begin to get some really odd questions."}]},{"cues":[{"time":825000,"text":"In the last Olympics, this gentleman,"},{"time":827000,"text":"who had several world records in the Special Olympics,"},{"time":831000,"text":"tried to run in the normal Olympics."},{"time":833000,"text":"The only issue with Oscar Pistorius"},{"time":835000,"text":"is he was born without bones in the lower part of his legs."},{"time":839000,"text":"He came within about a second of qualifying."},{"time":841000,"text":"He sued to be allowed to run,"},{"time":844000,"text":"and he won the suit,"},{"time":846000,"text":"but didn't qualify by time."},{"time":848000,"text":"Next Olympics, you can bet that Oscar, or one of Oscar's successors,"},{"time":853000,"text":"is going to make the time."},{"time":855000,"text":"And two or three Olympics after that, they are going to be unbeatable."}]},{"cues":[{"time":858000,"text":"And as you bring these trends together, and as you think of what it means"},{"time":863000,"text":"to take people who are profoundly deaf, who can now begin to hear --"},{"time":867000,"text":"I mean, remember the evolution of hearing aids, right?"},{"time":870000,"text":"I mean, your grandparents had these great big cones,"},{"time":873000,"text":"and then your parents had these odd boxes"},{"time":875000,"text":"that would squawk at odd times during dinner,"},{"time":877000,"text":"and now we have these little buds that nobody sees."},{"time":879000,"text":"And now you have cochlear implants"},{"time":881000,"text":"that go into people's heads and allow the deaf to begin to hear."},{"time":886000,"text":"Now, they can't hear as well as you and I can."},{"time":888000,"text":"But, in 10 or 15 machine generations they will,"},{"time":891000,"text":"and these are machine generations, not human generations."},{"time":894000,"text":"And about two or three years after they can hear as well as you and I can,"},{"time":898000,"text":"they'll be able to hear maybe how bats sing, or how whales talk,"},{"time":902000,"text":"or how dogs talk, and other types of tonal scales."},{"time":905000,"text":"They'll be able to focus their hearing,"},{"time":907000,"text":"they'll be able to increase the sensitivity, decrease the sensitivity,"},{"time":910000,"text":"do a series of things that we can't do."}]},{"cues":[{"time":912000,"text":"And the same thing is happening in eyes."},{"time":915000,"text":"This is a group in Germany that's beginning to engineer eyes"},{"time":918000,"text":"so that people who are blind can begin to see light and dark."},{"time":922000,"text":"Very primitive."},{"time":924000,"text":"And then they'll be able to see shape."},{"time":926000,"text":"And then they'll be able to see color, and then they'll be able to see in definition,"},{"time":929000,"text":"and one day, they'll see as well as you and I can."},{"time":932000,"text":"And a couple of years after that, they'll be able to see in ultraviolet,"},{"time":935000,"text":"they'll be able to see in infrared, they'll be able to focus their eyes,"},{"time":937000,"text":"they'll be able to come into a microfocus."},{"time":940000,"text":"They'll do stuff you and I can't do."},{"time":943000,"text":"All of these things are coming together,"},{"time":945000,"text":"and it's a particularly important thing to understand,"},{"time":949000,"text":"as we worry about the flames of the present,"},{"time":952000,"text":"to keep an eye on the future."}]},{"cues":[{"time":955000,"text":"And, of course, the future is looking back 200 years,"},{"time":958000,"text":"because next week is the 200th anniversary of Darwin's birth."},{"time":962000,"text":"And it's the 150th anniversary of the publication of \"The Origin of Species.\""},{"time":968000,"text":"And Darwin, of course, argued that evolution is a natural state."},{"time":972000,"text":"It is a natural state in everything that is alive, including hominids."},{"time":978000,"text":"There have actually been 22 species of hominids"},{"time":983000,"text":"that have been around, have evolved, have wandered in different places,"},{"time":987000,"text":"have gone extinct."},{"time":989000,"text":"It is common for hominids to evolve."},{"time":994000,"text":"And that's the reason why, as you look at the hominid fossil record,"},{"time":997000,"text":"erectus, and heidelbergensis, and floresiensis, and Neanderthals,"},{"time":1005000,"text":"and Homo sapiens, all overlap."},{"time":1010000,"text":"The common state of affairs is to have overlapping versions of hominids,"},{"time":1015000,"text":"not one."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1017000,"text":"And as you think of the implications of that,"},{"time":1019000,"text":"here's a brief history of the universe."},{"time":1021000,"text":"The universe was created 13.7 billion years ago,"},{"time":1024000,"text":"and then you created all the stars, and all the planets,"},{"time":1026000,"text":"and all the galaxies, and all the Milky Ways."},{"time":1028000,"text":"And then you created Earth about 4.5 billion years ago,"},{"time":1031000,"text":"and then you got life about four billion years ago,"},{"time":1034000,"text":"and then you got hominids about 0.006 billion years ago,"},{"time":1038000,"text":"and then you got our version of hominids about 0.0015 billion years ago."},{"time":1043000,"text":"Ta-dah!"},{"time":1045000,"text":"Maybe the reason for thr creation of the universe,"},{"time":1047000,"text":"and all the galaxies, and all the planets, and all the energy,"},{"time":1050000,"text":"and all the dark energy, and all the rest of stuff"},{"time":1052000,"text":"is to create what's in this room."},{"time":1056000,"text":"Maybe not."},{"time":1059000,"text":"That would be a mildly arrogant viewpoint."},{"time":1062000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":1067000,"text":"So, if that's not the purpose of the universe, then what's next?"},{"time":1072000,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1076000,"text":"I think what we're going to see is we're going to see a different species of hominid."},{"time":1081000,"text":"I think we're going to move from a Homo sapiens into a Homo evolutis."},{"time":1085000,"text":"And I think this isn't 1,000 years out."},{"time":1087000,"text":"I think most of us are going to glance at it,"},{"time":1090000,"text":"and our grandchildren are going to begin to live it."},{"time":1092000,"text":"And a Homo evolutis brings together these three trends"},{"time":1095000,"text":"into a hominid that takes direct and deliberate control"},{"time":1098000,"text":"over the evolution of his species, her species and other species."},{"time":1103000,"text":"And that, of course, would be the ultimate reboot."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1107000,"text":"Thank you very much."},{"time":1109000,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}